{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"137cd7fe-9c85-4207-8362-de31bd97bcc9","content":"Here's the concrete plan. I'll tailor examples to your .NET 10 SDK (`10.0.201`), but the steps apply to any version.\n\n---\n\n## Building a MAUI Android App on Headless Linux CI\n\n### Step 1 — Install the MAUI workload\n\n```bash\n# Use the stable SDK\nexport DOTNET_ROOT=/usr/share/dotnet\ndotnet workload install maui-android\n```\n\nThis pulls in the Android SDK build tools, platform APIs, and MAUI templates.\n\n### Step 2 — Find the Android SDK path the workload installed\n\n```bash\n# The workload installs Android pieces under a packs directory:\nfind \"$DOTNET_ROOT\" -path '*/Microsoft.Android.Sdk*' -name 'Sdk' -type d | head -1\n```\n\nMAUI's build targets need `ANDROID_HOME` or rely on the SDK bundled inside the workload pack. Typically **no separate Android SDK install is required** — the workload includes what's needed to compile. However, if your project targets a specific `compileSdkVersion` or uses `adb`/emulators, continue to Step 3.\n\n### Step 3 — (If needed) Install standalone Android command-line tools\n\n```bash\n# 1. Install JDK (required by Android tooling)\nsudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y openjdk-17-jdk-headless unzip wget\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64\n\n# 2. Download Android command-line tools\nexport ANDROID_HOME=$HOME/android-sdk\nmkdir -p \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools\"\nwget -q https://dl.google.com/android/repository/commandlinetools-linux-11076708_latest.zip -O /tmp/cmdline-tools.zip\nunzip -q /tmp/cmdline-tools.zip -d \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools\"\nmv \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/cmdline-tools\" \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/latest\"\n\n# 3. Find the correct platform/build-tools versions for YOUR project\n#    Look in your .csproj for <TargetFramework>net10.0-android</TargetFramework>\n#    or <SupportedOSPlatformVersion>. Then check the defaults:\ngrep -r 'TargetFramework\\|AndroidSdkVersion\\|SupportedOSPlatform' *.csproj\n\n#    The TFM \"net10.0-android\" defaults to API 35.\n#    \"net9.0-android\" defaults to API 35 as well (34 for earlier patches).\n#    Override with <AndroidSdkVersion> in .csproj if needed.\n\n# 4. Accept licenses and install matching components\nyes | \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/latest/bin/sdkmanager\" --licenses\n\"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/latest/bin/sdkmanager\" \\\n    \"platforms;android-35\" \\\n    \"build-tools;35.0.0\" \\\n    \"platform-tools\"\n```\n\n### Step 4 — Build\n\n```bash\nexport ANDROID_HOME=$HOME/android-sdk   # or skip if workload-only\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64\n\ndotnet build -f net10.0-android -c Release\n\n# For a signed APK/AAB:\ndotnet publish -f net10.0-android -c Release \\\n    -p:AndroidKeyStore=true \\\n    -p:AndroidSigningKeyStore=mykey.keystore \\\n    -p:AndroidSigningKeyAlias=myalias \\\n    -p:AndroidSigningKeyPass=env:KEYSTORE_PASS \\\n    -p:AndroidSigningStorePass=env:KEYSTORE_PASS\n```\n\n### How to find the right versions\n\n| What | Where to look |\n|---|---|\n| **Android API level** | Your `.csproj` `TargetFramework` (`net10.0-android` → API 35) |\n| **Build-tools version** | Match major version to API level (e.g., `35.0.0` for API 35) |\n| **JDK version** | [MAUI docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/maui/): JDK 17 for .NET 9+/10 |\n| **cmdline-tools URL** | [Android Studio downloads page](https://developer.android.com/studio#command-line-tools-only) |\n\n### Quick troubleshooting\n\n- **\"Android SDK not found\"** → Set `ANDROID_HOME` and pass `-p:AndroidSdkDirectory=$ANDROID_HOME`\n- **\"license not accepted\"** → Run `sdkmanager --licenses` with `yes |`\n- **JDK errors** → Ensure `JAVA_HOME` points to JDK 17, not 21+\n\nStep 3 is only needed if the workload alone doesn't satisfy your build. Try Step 1 → Step 4 first — it often just works.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"59c731c3-2f59-4a68-b293-d5317956e8d8","outputTokens":1247,"requestId":"DC09:33128B:7A9CF:9B12F:69F549F3"},"id":"1fe26c43-c9d0-443d-ac80-e3f4a573f913","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:49:15.660Z","parentId":"f87217ac-c66f-4adb-91a9-68c0c6a6e4b9"}
